rp prose, Armstrong has built a whole metaphysical system, that is, a comprehensive and unified picture of the fundamental structure of the world. The various chapters of the book address the key issues concerning Armstrong' view about the problem of universals, the nature of states of affairs, the ontological ground of possibility, nomic necessity, and dispositions, the truthmaker theory, and the theory of mind. This volume aims to celebrate Armstrong’s memory bringing new understanding, and hopefully stimulating more work, on his philosophy, with the conviction that it constitutes an invaluable heritage for contemporary research in metaphysics.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 23. Jul 2020) 0aMetaphysics. 0aRealism. 0aSciencexPhilosophy. 4aLaws of Nature, Scientific Realism, Naturalism, Theory of Mind, Truthmaker. 4aNaturalismus. 4aNaturgesetz. 4aTheorie des Geistes. 4aWahrmacher. 4aWissenschaftlicher Realismus. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Metaphysics.2bisacsh1 aCalemi, Francesco Federico, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2016z978311070100508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2016z9783110485103oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Philosophy 2016z9783110485301oZDB-23-DPH0 cEPUBz97831104550070 cprintz978311045461140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311045591540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110455915423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9783110455915.jpg  a978-3-11-070100-5  DG Plus eBook-Package 2016b2016  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK